<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
    <title>Trishul's Web</title>
    
    <style>
        /* This tells CSS to look for the element with the class name "bike-container" */
        .bike-container {
            display: flex; /* This is the magic command that puts things side-by-side */
            gap: 20px;     /* This adds a nice little space between the two bikes */
        }

        /* Let's also make the images look a bit neater */
        figure {
            margin: 0; /* Removes default browser spacing around the figures */
            border: 1px solid #ccc; /* Adds a light grey border */
            padding: 10px; /* Adds space inside the border */
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <h1>My First web</h1>
    <p>There isn't anything to see here😔 OR... </p>
    <p>Here Are Photos Of Two Greatest Bikes Ever Made.</p>
    
    <div class="bike-container">
        
        <figure>
            <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/33/91/de/3391de4e4bf73ecae8583c0473af8823.jpg" alt="Canyon" width="100">
            <figcaption>Canyon! The Rolls Royce Of Bikes With A Bunch Of Sensors And Even Hill Climb Assist. Here's A Video Of <a href="https://youtu.be/iq9mVy8Awto?si=JlZsyrolIB_yl8Yr">Canyon</a>.</figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure>
            <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/d6/3f/0f/d63f0fb8149a3322602edfb6aafc9348.jpg" alt="Colnago" width="150">
            <figcaption>Colnago! The Bugatti Of Bikes. Here's A Video Featuring <a href="https://youtu.be/-9XaWj2yevI?si=TiUqD-gSF9V6L3p7">Colnago</a>.</figcaption>
        </figure>

    </div>
    
</body>

</html>
